# Jira Direct REST API Rule

## Why this rule exists
The Atlassian MCP plugin is **blocked by Red Hat organization policy**. All Jira interactions must use the direct REST API via `curl` and the helper script at `scripts/jira-api.sh`.

## Connection details
- **Base URL:** `https://redhat.atlassian.net/rest/api/3`
- **Auth:** HTTP Basic — `yiyu@redhat.com` + token from `~/.jira-token`
- **Search endpoint:** `POST /rest/api/3/search/jql` (the old `GET /rest/api/2/search` has been removed)

## Helper script
Source the script before using any function:
```bash
source scripts/jira-api.sh
```

### Available functions
| Function | Usage |
|---|---|
| `jira_search "<JQL>"` | Search issues (POST /search/jql) |
| `jira_get_issue "KEY"` | Get a single issue |
| `jira_create_issue '<json>'` | Create an issue |
| `jira_edit_issue "KEY" '<json>'` | Update an issue |
| `jira_transition_issue "KEY" '<json>'` | Transition issue status |
| `jira_get_transitions "KEY"` | List available transitions |
| `jira_add_comment "KEY" "text"` | Add a comment (ADF format) |
| `jira_lookup_user "name"` | Search users by name/email |
| `jira_link_issues "type" "KEY-1" "KEY-2"` | Link two issues |

## UXD custom field IDs
| Field | ID | Type | Applies to |
|---|---|---|---|
| Story Points | `customfield_10028` | number | Stories only |
| Size | `customfield_10795` | select: XS / S / M / L / XL | Epics only |
| Activity Type | `customfield_10464` | select: Orient / Explore / Make / Monitor / Consult / Enable | All |
| Epic Link | `customfield_10014` | string (epic key) | Stories/Tasks |

## Output formatting
- Format Jira results as **markdown tables**
- Link issue keys to `https://issues.redhat.com/browse/{KEY}`
- Example: `[CPUX-1234](https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CPUX-1234)`

## Authentication errors
If a `401 Unauthorized` is returned, instruct the user to regenerate their API token at:
https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens

## Security
- **NEVER** commit `~/.jira-token` or embed the token in code/commits
- The token file lives outside the repo at `~/.jira-token` with `chmod 600`
